   "source": [
    "# 26.1 What is Multicollinearity? How to detect it? List some techniques to overcome Multicollinearity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "8415c1fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "What is Multicollinearity?\n",
    "\n",
    "Multicollinearity occurs when two or more independent variables are highly correlated with each other in a dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 This means:\n",
    "\n",
    "Features carry redundant information\n",
    "Model struggles to identify the true impact of each feature\n",
    "⚠️ Why is it a problem?\n",
    "Coefficients become unstable\n",
    "Hard to interpret feature importance\n",
    "Small data changes → big coefficient changes\n",
    "Especially problematic in linear models like Linear Regression\n",
    "🔍 How to Detect Multicollinearity?\n",
    "🔹 1. Correlation Matrix\n",
    "Check pairwise correlations\n",
    "If correlation > 0.8 or 0.9 → strong multicollinearity\n",
    "🔹 2. Variance Inflation Factor (VIF) (Most Important)\n",
    "\n",
    "VIF=\n",
    "1−R\n",
    "2\n",
    "1\n",
    "\t​\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Measures how much variance is inflated\n",
    "Rule of thumb:\n",
    "VIF = 1 → no correlation\n",
    "VIF > 5 or 10 → high multicollinearity\n",
    "🔹 3. Eigenvalues / Condition Number\n",
    "Used in advanced analysis\n",
    "Large condition number → multicollinearity\n",
    "🔹 4. Unstable Coefficients\n",
    "Coefficients change drastically when data changes\n",
    "🚀 How to Handle Multicollinearity?\n",
    "✅ 1. Remove Highly Correlated Features\n",
    "Drop one of the correlated variables\n",
    "✔️ Simple and effective\n",
    "✅ 2. Feature Selection\n",
    "Keep only important features\n",
    "✅ 3. Combine Features\n",
    "Create new feature (e.g., average, ratio)\n",
    "✅ 4. Use Dimensionality Reduction\n",
    "Techniques like Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Converts correlated variables → uncorrelated components\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 5. Regularization Techniques\n",
    "Ridge Regression (L2) → reduces coefficient variance\n",
    "Lasso Regression (L1) → can remove features\n",
    "✅ 6. Use Tree-Based Models\n",
    "Less affected by multicollinearity\n",
    "🎯 Interview-Ready Answer (Short)**\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Multicollinearity occurs when independent variables are highly correlated, causing instability in model coefficients. It can be detected using correlation matrices and VIF, and handled by removing correlated features, using PCA, or applying regularization techniques like Ridge or Lasso regression.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip\n",
    "\n",
    "Say this line 👇\n",
    "👉 “Multicollinearity affects interpretability more than prediction accuracy.”"
   ]
  },
